# kit-manifest — the harness-kit SHIP CONTRACT: the single declarative source
# for which files the kit installs, which ownership layer each belongs to, and
# which previously-shipped paths are retired. install-lib.sh derives every
# file set from this file (there are no hard-coded inventory lists); check
# #9c derives manifest-completeness from it; the kit's update mode reads the
# NEW kit's copy to decide what to replace, add, and remove.
#
# Format: one entry per line —
#   <layer> <repo-relative path> [dest=<repo-relative install path>]
# Fields are whitespace-separated; '#' lines and blank lines are ignored.
# The optional dest= field is reserved for entries installed under a
# different name (unused by the scripts/ tree, whose paths ARE their
# destinations).
#
# Layers:
#   mechanism        Copied verbatim at init; update REPLACES it while the
#                    installed copy still matches its integrity pin.
#   policy           Template copied at init, owned by the repo after: update
#                    only ever DIFFS it, even when pristine and unmarked.
#   optional-policy  Authored per repo (never copied from the kit); when
#                    present it is integrity-pinned and diff-only, like policy.
#   retired          No longer shipped. Update REMOVES the installed copy only
#                    when it is pristine (sha still matches its pin) and not
#                    '# tailored'; drifted or tailored copies are kept and
#                    reported for manual review — retirement never deletes
#                    local changes.
#
# This file is itself mechanism: integrity-pinned in scripts/.harness-manifest
# and protected by guard-config.sh — it tells update what to overwrite and
# delete, which makes it the most security-sensitive shipped file after the
# integrity manifest. Ship a new file by adding its line here; stop shipping
# one by MOVING its line to the retired layer (never just deleting the line).

# --- mechanism: install/update/check machinery --------------------------------
mechanism scripts/kit-manifest
mechanism scripts/install-lib.sh
mechanism scripts/check-harness.sh
mechanism scripts/sync-agent-skills.sh
mechanism scripts/dev-instance.sh
mechanism scripts/log-lib.sh
mechanism scripts/audit-log.sh
mechanism scripts/doc-garden.sh
mechanism scripts/eval-lib.sh
mechanism scripts/eval.sh
mechanism scripts/eval-harness.sh

# --- mechanism: regression suites ---------------------------------------------
# The kit's own conformance suites (install/update/recovery, the checker
# suite, eval integrity, fixture isolation) are maintainer-only since
# v0.22.0 — see the retired section. Adopters keep the hook behavioral
# tests, the runtime suites below, and the post-init/post-update smoke test.
mechanism scripts/test-harness-smoke.sh
mechanism scripts/test-dev-instance.sh
mechanism scripts/test-log.sh
mechanism scripts/test-audit-log.sh
mechanism scripts/test-doc-garden.sh
mechanism scripts/test-verify.sh

